<AnimatePresence>
    {activeParagraphId && (
        <ParagraphCommentPanel
            postId={postData?.journalId}
            paragraphId={activeParagraphId}
            receiverId={postData?.userId}
            onClose={() => setActiveParagraphId(null)}
        />
    )}
</AnimatePresence>
```

---

## 9. Migration Strategy for Existing Content

Existing journal posts do not have `paragraphId` properties in their Lexical JSON. Two approaches:

**Lazy migration (recommended):** When the comment counts endpoint is hit for a post whose content lacks `paragraphId` values, it returns an empty counts object. The paragraph IDs are only assigned when the author next saves/edits the post. This means paragraph commenting is only available on newly saved content.

**Eager migration (optional, for launch):** A one-time script walks all journals, parses the content JSON, assigns paragraph IDs, and re-saves. Similar pattern to the existing `server/scripts/backfillUsernames.js`.

I recommend lazy migration initially, with the eager migration script available as a follow-up once the feature is proven.

